reviews.text: Great atmosphere, service and food. It is pricey but you get what you paid for. Perfect for taking the family.

Outstanding Chinese food, just the right amount of fusion. Amazing presentation, sublime atmosphere and delectable food, probably my favourite Chinese restaurant in HK, thank you for an extraordinary meal. Forgot to mention the superb professionalism of the staff...
a must if you are staying at Landmark, the food here is really good. i recommend to course menu and the shark fin! worth every penny!

The food is way better than the china club ...very well appointed and has a great bar area. The Peking duck and the roast pork are must haves and there are plenty of private rooms you can book out for a business discussion. Decor is typical the late David Tang beaux arts chinois and a great example to the style of this tastemaker who made Chinois cool in Chelsea
Upper class mall. They put a lot of money into the holiday decorations.
